🚀 Portfolio Automation Agent
This portfolio is equipped with a GitHub Actions CI/CD Agent that automatically synchronizes my latest projects from various repositories into the showcase section below.

🛠️ How it Works
The automation follows a Push-to-Sync architecture to ensure this site remains a living document of my technical journey without manual intervention.

1. The Trigger

Whenever a new project repository is created or updated (and tagged with a specific topic or pushed to main), a GitHub Action is triggered in that specific project's repo.

2. The Logic (The Agent)

The agent performs the following steps:

Authentication: Uses a GitHub Fine-grained PAT (Personal Access Token) to securely gain write access to this repository.

Data Extraction: Fetches metadata from the project repository, including:

Repository Name

Description (used as the project blurb)

Topics/Tags (used for filtering)

GitHub URL

Data Transformation: A Python script parses the existing _data/projects.yml file, inserts or updates the project entry, and ensures the YAML structure remains valid.

3. Deployment

Once the _data/projects.yml file is updated and pushed back to this repo, GitHub Pages automatically triggers a new Jekyll build, and the live site updates within seconds.

📂 Project Structure for Automation
_data/projects.yml: The "Source of Truth" for all displayed projects.

.github/workflows/: Contains the logic for any site-wide maintenance tasks.